1
00:00:09,467 --> 00:00:12,033
<i>Love, your phone's ringing.
It's just a number.</i>

2
00:00:12,167 --> 00:00:13,767
<i> I'll answer it, okay?</i>

3
00:00:13,900 --> 00:00:15,133
<i> No, no! I got it!</i>

4
00:00:15,267 --> 00:00:16,167
<i> I got it!</i>

5
00:00:16,300 --> 00:00:17,033
<i> Hello?</i>

6
00:00:17,167 --> 00:00:18,767
<i> Hello? Who's this?</i>

7
00:00:18,900 --> 00:00:20,300
<i> It's a woman.</i>

8
00:00:20,433 --> 00:00:24,533
<i>Her voice sounds familiar.
I just can't place it.</i>

9
00:00:24,667 --> 00:00:27,000
<i>Mom, how did you find out
Dad was cheating</i>

10
00:00:27,133 --> 00:00:29,700
<i> when you were still together?</i>

11
00:01:19,000 --> 00:01:21,567
Marj, haven't we already
talked about this?

12
00:01:21,700 --> 00:01:25,033
If you really wanna help,
just give me some space.

13
00:01:25,167 --> 00:01:26,267
I need to focus.

14
00:01:26,400 --> 00:01:28,567
Love, please.
Just three minutes.

15
00:01:28,700 --> 00:01:31,733
If you don't like it,
I'll understand.

16
00:01:31,867 --> 00:01:34,133
I feel really guilty about
what happened at the party,

17
00:01:34,267 --> 00:01:37,133
and I know work's been tough
for you.

18
00:01:38,167 --> 00:01:41,400
Paolo, I don't want
you resenting me.

19
00:01:41,567 --> 00:01:44,700
That's how marriages fall apart.

20
00:01:44,833 --> 00:01:48,200
So please,
let me make it up to you.

21
00:01:48,333 --> 00:01:49,300
Please?

22
00:01:51,400 --> 00:01:52,367
Fine.

23
00:01:54,000 --> 00:01:56,167
So what's your suggestion?
What's your solution?

24
00:02:04,367 --> 00:02:08,100
Mrs. Sutherland,
thank you for giving us time.

25
00:02:08,233 --> 00:02:10,900
My husband has something good
to offer to you.

26
00:02:11,033 --> 00:02:12,233
What kind of offer?

27
00:02:14,100 --> 00:02:16,333
We'll be direct with you,
Mrs. Sutherland.

28
00:02:16,500 --> 00:02:19,600
We're offering you
a Menagerie Manor unit

29
00:02:19,733 --> 00:02:21,500
at a preferential rate.

30
00:02:21,633 --> 00:02:22,933
Preferential rate?

31
00:02:23,767 --> 00:02:25,167
What do you mean?

32
00:02:25,300 --> 00:02:26,433
For you,

33
00:02:26,567 --> 00:02:28,733
we're lowering the price
of a Menagerie unit

34
00:02:28,867 --> 00:02:30,333
to 50 million pesos.

35
00:02:31,533 --> 00:02:32,400
Wow!

36
00:02:32,533 --> 00:02:34,067
For real?

37
00:02:34,767 --> 00:02:37,200
That big of a discount?

38
00:02:38,933 --> 00:02:40,600
So you mean...

39
00:02:40,733 --> 00:02:42,367
a huge discount.

40
00:02:42,500 --> 00:02:44,267
Yes, Mrs. Sutherland.

41
00:02:44,400 --> 00:02:46,867
But this comes with an...

42
00:02:48,200 --> 00:02:49,800
exchange arrangement.

43
00:02:51,333 --> 00:02:52,733
Oh, so there's a catch?

44
00:02:55,467 --> 00:02:57,067
Yes.

45
00:02:57,200 --> 00:02:58,033
First,

46
00:02:58,167 --> 00:03:00,233
strict confidentiality.

47
00:03:00,367 --> 00:03:04,800
No one else can know the rate
we're giving you.

48
00:03:04,933 --> 00:03:07,367
Second, referrals.

49
00:03:07,500 --> 00:03:10,667
Strictly within
your private circles.

50
00:03:10,800 --> 00:03:14,433
Only five people are getting
this discounted offer.

51
00:03:14,567 --> 00:03:16,633
Your referrals, however,

52
00:03:16,767 --> 00:03:19,900
will be offered
the full market price.

53
00:03:22,433 --> 00:03:26,733
I'm not against the arrangement.

54
00:03:26,867 --> 00:03:28,800
If the discount is that big,

55
00:03:28,933 --> 00:03:31,767
I think my spouse might actually
consider it.

56
00:03:33,500 --> 00:03:36,800
This is a good idea. Actually,
I got the idea from you.

57
00:03:36,933 --> 00:03:39,233
I suddenly came up
with a plan

58
00:03:39,367 --> 00:03:41,867
when we started talking
about discounts.

59
00:03:42,000 --> 00:03:44,767
Oh, right! That makes sense.

60
00:03:44,900 --> 00:03:48,533
No wonder you hugged me
so tight that day.

61
00:03:48,667 --> 00:03:52,867
If I were you, Mrs. Sutherland,
I wouldn't let go of this deal.

62
00:03:53,000 --> 00:03:56,533
Real estate companies
rarely give discounts this big.

63
00:04:05,533 --> 00:04:07,967
I'm starting to lose
patience, Edward.

64
00:04:09,333 --> 00:04:13,867
You still haven't given me
anything useful on Paolo.

65
00:04:15,633 --> 00:04:17,267
I'm trying.

66
00:04:17,400 --> 00:04:19,633
What you're asking isn't easy.

67
00:04:19,767 --> 00:04:22,533
If I get caught, I'm done.

68
00:04:24,933 --> 00:04:26,967
What's so hard about it?

69
00:04:28,933 --> 00:04:33,000
I just need you to access your
brother's personal computer,

70
00:04:33,133 --> 00:04:35,833
which is just a few feet away
from you at home.

71
00:04:35,967 --> 00:04:38,400
If it's that easy, why
don't you do it yourself?

72
00:04:42,233 --> 00:04:44,367
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

73
00:04:45,400 --> 00:04:46,733
Shall we proceed,
Mrs. Torrecampo?

74
00:04:46,867 --> 00:04:48,033
Of course.

75
00:04:48,167 --> 00:04:49,133
Mrs. Torrecampo,

76
00:04:49,267 --> 00:04:51,867
there were rumors your sons
had a disagreement

77
00:04:52,000 --> 00:04:53,667
during a company event.

78
00:04:53,800 --> 00:04:55,067
Is that true?

79
00:04:57,967 --> 00:05:00,700
You know what, "disagreement"
is a very generous word...

80
00:05:00,867 --> 00:05:03,633
but that story isn't true.

81
00:05:04,667 --> 00:05:08,433
Don't believe everything you
hear.

82
00:05:08,567 --> 00:05:10,133
In real estate,

83
00:05:10,267 --> 00:05:14,533
rumors are cheaper than land and
much easier to manufacture,

84
00:05:14,667 --> 00:05:19,767
especially for people
who can't keep up.

85
00:05:19,900 --> 00:05:22,400
Torrecampo Realty
has been very visible lately,

86
00:05:22,533 --> 00:05:25,967
and when you're ahead,
people don't chase you.

87
00:05:26,100 --> 00:05:28,467
They throw stones
and hope it sticks.

88
00:05:29,800 --> 00:05:33,333
But for now, why don't we talk
about something worth printing?

89
00:05:33,467 --> 00:05:36,967
As I mentioned before,
this is Mrs. Bautista,

90
00:05:37,133 --> 00:05:38,467
the head of our SPED school,

91
00:05:38,600 --> 00:05:41,900
where I'll be conducting
an outreach project.

92
00:05:42,033 --> 00:05:43,533
Yes, Ma'am Regina.

93
00:05:43,667 --> 00:05:45,967
We truly appreciate
your continued support

94
00:05:46,100 --> 00:05:48,800
for the Learning Hearts Special
Education Center.

95
00:05:48,933 --> 00:05:50,533
Always happy to help.

96
00:05:50,667 --> 00:05:52,267
Your foundation and sponsorship

97
00:05:52,400 --> 00:05:54,300
have helped many
of our students.

98
00:05:57,200 --> 00:06:00,367
Manang Yolly said she'd
buy me a burger, Mom!

99
00:06:00,500 --> 00:06:01,567
Jobert.

100
00:06:03,600 --> 00:06:05,067
Jobert!

101
00:06:05,200 --> 00:06:06,400
It's you!

102
00:06:09,167 --> 00:06:10,733
Did you really think

103
00:06:10,867 --> 00:06:13,633
people in this building
don't already know

104
00:06:13,767 --> 00:06:15,367
you and your brother
fought again?

105
00:06:17,200 --> 00:06:20,433
Everyone thinks Paolo won,

106
00:06:21,633 --> 00:06:23,300
and you lost.

107
00:06:26,533 --> 00:06:29,667
If you don't do something
to take him down,

108
00:06:30,700 --> 00:06:33,000
you'll be branded a loser
for life.

109
00:06:35,267 --> 00:06:39,867
And if Project Menagerie
succeeds under your brother,

110
00:06:40,000 --> 00:06:42,433
he'll look even better
to your dad.

111
00:06:44,400 --> 00:06:45,933
And you?

112
00:06:46,067 --> 00:06:47,700
What do you think
happens to you?

113
00:06:50,033 --> 00:06:52,100
You'll look even smaller
in everyone's eyes.

114
00:06:54,100 --> 00:06:55,700
Is that what you want?

115
00:07:01,700 --> 00:07:03,633
Ma'am, he's one of our alumni.

116
00:07:03,767 --> 00:07:07,567
A scholar
under Miss Regina's sponsorship.

117
00:07:07,700 --> 00:07:11,067
If I'm not mistaken, he's now
working at Torrecampo Realty?

118
00:07:11,200 --> 00:07:13,400
- Yes, yes.
- Wow!

119
00:07:13,533 --> 00:07:14,400
Wait.

120
00:07:14,567 --> 00:07:16,500
Why don't we include
him in the outreach?

121
00:07:16,633 --> 00:07:19,467
We can feature
him, too, right?

122
00:07:19,600 --> 00:07:23,067
It'll add a very personal
touch to your profile.

123
00:07:23,200 --> 00:07:24,733
Oh, yes, of course!

124
00:07:24,867 --> 00:07:28,333
I mean,
we should always remind people

125
00:07:28,467 --> 00:07:31,767
where success begins, right?

126
00:07:31,900 --> 00:07:36,000
And we should never forget
those we've helped,

127
00:07:36,133 --> 00:07:39,400
and who help make us look good.

128
00:07:43,567 --> 00:07:45,267
We'll head inside now.

129
00:07:45,400 --> 00:07:46,133
Excuse us.

130
00:07:46,267 --> 00:07:48,367
Jobert, let's go inside.

131
00:07:48,533 --> 00:07:49,833
Thank you, Ma'am.

132
00:08:00,400 --> 00:08:02,933
Please, have something to drink.
Grab some snacks.

133
00:08:03,067 --> 00:08:04,633
Thank you.

134
00:08:33,133 --> 00:08:35,500
Thank you so much,
Mrs. Sutherland.

135
00:08:35,633 --> 00:08:37,967
Your husband should be
the one thanking you.

136
00:08:38,100 --> 00:08:40,967
You're doing everything
you can to help him.

137
00:08:45,333 --> 00:08:46,867
She said you're lucky
to have me.

138
00:08:49,100 --> 00:08:50,633
Thank you.

139
00:08:50,767 --> 00:08:52,767
I'm very lucky, I know.

140
00:08:54,000 --> 00:08:56,900
Well, congratulations!

141
00:08:58,267 --> 00:08:59,900
- Congratulations.
- Thank you.

142
00:09:00,033 --> 00:09:02,600
- Congratulations.
- Thank you so much.

143
00:09:04,433 --> 00:09:08,700
And I'm glad I got to work
with you again.

144
00:09:11,900 --> 00:09:13,167
- Keep in touch.
- Thanks.

145
00:09:13,300 --> 00:09:14,700
- Congratulations again.
- Thank you very much.

146
00:09:14,833 --> 00:09:16,900
- I'll head out now, okay?
- Sure.

147
00:09:17,033 --> 00:09:19,067
Okay, bye!

148
00:09:25,900 --> 00:09:27,233
You did it.

149
00:09:27,400 --> 00:09:29,967
This project's
going to be a success.

150
00:09:30,100 --> 00:09:31,700
Congratulations, Love.

151
00:09:34,367 --> 00:09:35,633
No, we did it.

152
00:09:44,600 --> 00:09:45,933
Come with me.

153
00:09:53,033 --> 00:09:54,533
Everyone!

154
00:09:54,667 --> 00:09:55,967
Everyone, please.

155
00:10:00,800 --> 00:10:03,300
Mrs. Sutherland
just signed.

156
00:10:03,433 --> 00:10:05,433
Menagerie Manor
officially has a buyer.

157
00:10:10,533 --> 00:10:13,500
And I couldn't have done this
without you.

158
00:10:44,033 --> 00:10:46,700
This looks good on you.

159
00:10:47,367 --> 00:10:49,867
Just pick whatever you
want to wear

160
00:10:50,000 --> 00:10:52,833
for your outreach program, okay?

161
00:10:52,967 --> 00:10:54,833
Thank you, Uncle Greg.

162
00:10:54,967 --> 00:10:56,767
You're so nice.

163
00:10:56,900 --> 00:10:58,200
Thank you.

164
00:11:02,867 --> 00:11:04,133
Jobert.

165
00:11:05,300 --> 00:11:07,267
Mom, look!

166
00:11:07,400 --> 00:11:11,033
I've got so many clothes.
Uncle Greg gave them to me.

167
00:11:11,200 --> 00:11:12,433
Yeah.

168
00:11:16,300 --> 00:11:17,300
Greg?

169
00:11:30,300 --> 00:11:32,400
I know what you're doing.

170
00:11:34,333 --> 00:11:36,800
You're getting close to Jobert

171
00:11:38,067 --> 00:11:39,667
because you think...

172
00:11:41,200 --> 00:11:43,600
it'll make me warm up to you.

173
00:11:47,733 --> 00:11:51,267
But can you not use
my child like that?

174
00:11:54,000 --> 00:11:56,200
I'm sorry, Evelyn.

175
00:11:56,333 --> 00:11:58,333
I'm just not used
to being rejected.

176
00:11:59,733 --> 00:12:01,933
So the effect is...

177
00:12:02,067 --> 00:12:03,633
it makes me try even harder.

178
00:12:04,667 --> 00:12:07,633
I keep trying and trying

179
00:12:07,767 --> 00:12:10,233
until things go my way.

180
00:12:13,067 --> 00:12:16,600
Well, let me make this clear.

181
00:12:16,767 --> 00:12:20,400
That's never going to happen.

182
00:12:22,067 --> 00:12:25,500
I'm not as weak...

183
00:12:25,633 --> 00:12:26,833
as I used to be.

184
00:12:28,767 --> 00:12:31,600
So, can you stop
wasting your time?

185
00:12:38,833 --> 00:12:40,133
We'll see.

186
00:12:45,300 --> 00:12:46,500
I'll go ahead.

187
00:12:47,600 --> 00:12:49,267
- Sir.
- Yolly.

188
00:12:51,667 --> 00:12:52,900
Excuse me, Ma'am.

189
00:12:55,367 --> 00:12:57,000
Hi, Jobert.

190
00:12:57,133 --> 00:12:58,600
Manang Yolly.

191
00:13:28,267 --> 00:13:30,633
I didn't think it would work.

192
00:13:30,767 --> 00:13:32,133
I really didn't.

193
00:13:32,267 --> 00:13:34,300
But good thing
you thought of it.

194
00:13:41,033 --> 00:13:42,100
Love...

195
00:13:44,267 --> 00:13:45,133
why?

196
00:13:46,333 --> 00:13:48,033
You pulled it off.

197
00:13:48,167 --> 00:13:49,433
You know that, right?

198
00:13:51,867 --> 00:13:53,900
Don't worry.

199
00:13:54,033 --> 00:13:55,767
These are tears of joy.

200
00:13:57,567 --> 00:13:59,967
I was just scared that

201
00:14:00,100 --> 00:14:03,367
if it didn't work,
you'd still be mad at me.

202
00:14:07,167 --> 00:14:08,933
Marj...

203
00:14:09,067 --> 00:14:10,367
listen.

204
00:14:11,400 --> 00:14:12,367
I'm tired.

205
00:14:13,900 --> 00:14:16,300
But that doesn't mean...

206
00:14:16,433 --> 00:14:17,700
I'm mad.

207
00:14:20,733 --> 00:14:22,367
And I'm really grateful

208
00:14:23,833 --> 00:14:25,100
you showed up for me.

209
00:14:41,367 --> 00:14:43,467
Damn that Paolo.

210
00:14:43,600 --> 00:14:46,033
He really had to flaunt it
right in front of me.

211
00:15:08,433 --> 00:15:10,067
I'm going to take a shower,
Love.

212
00:15:45,200 --> 00:15:46,567
Love?

213
00:15:47,800 --> 00:15:49,100
Love.

214
00:16:03,000 --> 00:16:05,167
Love, someone's calling you.

215
00:16:05,300 --> 00:16:06,600
Love?

216
00:16:09,367 --> 00:16:11,767
- Love?
- Hon?

217
00:16:11,900 --> 00:16:14,233
Someone's calling you.
It's just a number.

218
00:16:24,433 --> 00:16:25,933
Just a number?

219
00:16:26,067 --> 00:16:27,367
Yeah.

220
00:16:29,200 --> 00:16:30,433
Love, just ignore it.

221
00:16:30,567 --> 00:16:32,200
It's probably a wrong number.

222
00:16:34,300 --> 00:16:37,533
What if it's important?
I'll answer it, okay?

223
00:16:37,667 --> 00:16:38,733
No, no! I got it!

224
00:16:38,867 --> 00:16:39,833
I got it!

225
00:16:42,467 --> 00:16:44,867
- Hello?
- Hello? Who's this?

226
00:16:56,333 --> 00:16:58,200
Hello? Answer me.

227
00:17:10,633 --> 00:17:11,400
Damn it!

228
00:17:13,067 --> 00:17:14,533
Did she recognize my voice?

229
00:17:30,933 --> 00:17:31,867
Love...

230
00:17:34,467 --> 00:17:35,633
Who was that on the phone?

231
00:17:36,900 --> 00:17:38,967
They didn't say.
Just hung up right away.

232
00:17:45,300 --> 00:17:47,167
Probably just a wrong number.

233
00:17:53,700 --> 00:17:55,667
But it was a woman.

234
00:17:57,033 --> 00:17:58,667
Her voice sounded familiar.

235
00:17:58,800 --> 00:18:05,367
I just can't place who it was.

236
00:18:05,500 --> 00:18:07,267
Maybe she just dialed
the wrong number.

237
00:18:07,400 --> 00:18:08,933
See? She didn't call back,
right?

238
00:18:30,267 --> 00:18:33,300
Do you realize
how close that was last night?

239
00:18:33,433 --> 00:18:36,767
You called my cellphone
while I was at home,

240
00:18:36,900 --> 00:18:39,033
with my wife right there.

241
00:18:40,067 --> 00:18:42,367
I said I'm sorry!

242
00:18:44,233 --> 00:18:46,733
Good thing she didn't recognize
your voice.

243
00:18:46,867 --> 00:18:51,167
Because if you'd said anything
else, we're both done.

244
00:18:51,300 --> 00:18:55,100
That's why I hung up right away,
right?

245
00:18:55,267 --> 00:18:57,433
You know you're doing something
wrong,

246
00:18:57,567 --> 00:19:00,167
and you still let your wife
hold your phone?

247
00:19:00,300 --> 00:19:02,933
And now you're blaming me?

248
00:19:03,067 --> 00:19:05,733
You don't need to call me.
It's that simple.

249
00:19:06,767 --> 00:19:08,067
And why not?

250
00:19:09,700 --> 00:19:11,567
So that's it? Just like that?

251
00:19:13,567 --> 00:19:17,200
Thea, we can't afford
to be careless.

252
00:19:17,333 --> 00:19:19,500
We have to be more careful.

253
00:19:21,967 --> 00:19:25,600
Fine.
But you can't just ignore me.

254
00:19:25,733 --> 00:19:27,200
- Why are you here?
- Hon!

255
00:19:27,333 --> 00:19:28,767
What, you want round two?

256
00:19:28,933 --> 00:19:30,167
- Pao!
- Why?

257
00:19:30,300 --> 00:19:32,033
Are you surprised?

258
00:19:32,167 --> 00:19:34,067
I'm just here
to pick up my wife.

259
00:19:35,133 --> 00:19:36,833
I'll just grab my things.

260
00:19:37,767 --> 00:19:40,167
Paolo, let's continue
our discussion later,

261
00:19:40,300 --> 00:19:41,633
about the project, okay?

262
00:19:43,433 --> 00:19:53,400
Just wait for me here, hon.

263
00:19:56,533 --> 00:19:59,833
Sir, Mr. Zuriaga's meeting
is finished.

264
00:19:59,967 --> 00:20:01,933
He said he'll say goodbye
to you.

265
00:20:02,100 --> 00:20:03,200
Okay.

266
00:21:13,933 --> 00:21:15,367
You look pale.

267
00:21:16,000 --> 00:21:18,833
What?

268
00:21:18,967 --> 00:21:20,267
My head hurts.

269
00:21:21,467 --> 00:21:23,700
I'll just go to Thea's office.
Maybe...

270
00:21:23,833 --> 00:21:33,800
She has some medicine.

271
00:22:02,933 --> 00:22:08,667
Here, my sister said these are
fruits for people with leukemia.

272
00:22:08,800 --> 00:22:10,633
Just check with Jasmine's doctor
if it's okay.

273
00:22:11,633 --> 00:22:12,567
Thanks.

274
00:22:15,700 --> 00:22:19,100
Marj, do you want to eat
the fruits yourself?

275
00:22:19,233 --> 00:22:21,800
You need the energy.
You look drained.

276
00:22:21,933 --> 00:22:22,933
Is something wrong?

277
00:22:26,733 --> 00:22:28,567
Something happened last night.

278
00:22:29,233 --> 00:22:30,367
What happened?

279
00:22:32,300 --> 00:22:34,467
Someone called Paolo's phone.

280
00:22:35,900 --> 00:22:37,433
It was a woman.

281
00:22:39,633 --> 00:22:41,533
Did she say who she was?

282
00:22:41,667 --> 00:22:44,067
No. She hung up immediately.

283
00:22:44,200 --> 00:22:47,833
It's like she was surprised
I answered.

284
00:22:47,967 --> 00:22:50,600
But Hannah,
the voice sounds familiar.

285
00:22:51,767 --> 00:22:52,967
Familiar like how?

286
00:22:54,767 --> 00:22:56,433
Just familiar.

287
00:22:56,567 --> 00:23:00,367
I feel like I've heard it
before, but I can't place where.

288
00:23:03,433 --> 00:23:07,467
Marj, don't get mad, okay?

289
00:23:07,600 --> 00:23:09,533
But...

290
00:23:09,667 --> 00:23:13,767
doesn't this feel like
Paolo's old habits coming back?

291
00:23:13,900 --> 00:23:15,500
What habits?

292
00:23:15,633 --> 00:23:25,600
Maybe your husband's cheating
again?

293
00:23:44,567 --> 00:23:46,867
Marj?

294
00:23:47,000 --> 00:23:48,133
Are you okay?

295
00:23:49,467 --> 00:23:50,933
Yes, Mom I'm okay.

296
00:23:53,367 --> 00:23:55,167
Mom, how did you find out

297
00:23:55,300 --> 00:24:00,600
Dad was cheating
when you were still together?

298
00:24:07,500 --> 00:24:09,100
Why did you ask, Marj?

299
00:24:12,167 --> 00:24:16,000
I just wanted to know what
the signs are when a man cheats.

300
00:24:18,300 --> 00:24:20,267
The usual ones?

301
00:24:20,400 --> 00:24:22,367
Like with your dad.

302
00:24:22,500 --> 00:24:24,467
Lipstick on his collar,

303
00:24:24,600 --> 00:24:26,633
smelling like
someone else's perfume...

304
00:24:26,767 --> 00:24:27,967
that kind of thing.

305
00:24:30,800 --> 00:24:32,733
Why, Marj?

306
00:24:32,867 --> 00:24:35,467
Do you think
Paolo is cheating?

307
00:24:36,833 --> 00:24:38,433
I don't know, Mom.

308
00:24:39,633 --> 00:24:42,700
But maybe I need to check
his stuff.

309
00:24:42,833 --> 00:24:45,900
See if there's lipstick,
see if there's another perfume.

310
00:24:48,733 --> 00:24:50,133
Marj...

311
00:24:50,267 --> 00:24:52,200
you know, sweetie,
I used to be like that.

312
00:24:53,333 --> 00:24:54,400
But...

313
00:24:54,533 --> 00:25:01,200
guys these days seem to have
different tactics.

314
00:25:01,333 --> 00:25:02,900
They've gotten smarter, Marj.

315
00:25:04,733 --> 00:25:06,367
They know how to
hide things better.

316
00:25:08,033 --> 00:25:10,233
So nowadays,

317
00:25:10,367 --> 00:25:14,100
having evidence isn't enough,
sweetie.

318
00:25:14,233 --> 00:25:18,933
You need to be smarter than him.

319
00:25:27,400 --> 00:25:28,600
Oh my god.

320
00:25:28,733 --> 00:25:32,900
You even turned on the location
on his social media account?

321
00:25:33,033 --> 00:25:35,067
I just tried it once.

322
00:25:35,200 --> 00:25:38,600
And he's just at the office.

323
00:25:38,767 --> 00:25:40,867
Maybe I'm wrong.

324
00:25:41,000 --> 00:25:42,067
I hope so.

325
00:25:42,200 --> 00:25:43,900
Paolo's not at the office
anymore.

326
00:25:44,033 --> 00:25:45,033
Heading home?

327
00:25:45,167 --> 00:25:47,167
He's at the Olympo Hotel.

328
00:25:47,300 --> 00:25:48,867
What's Paolo
doing at a hotel?

329
00:25:49,000 --> 00:25:50,333
- Hello?
- Hello, love?

330
00:25:50,467 --> 00:25:52,033
- Are you at the office?
- I'm just at the office.

331
00:25:52,167 --> 00:25:54,100
I'll finish this
and call you back, okay?

332
00:25:54,233 --> 00:25:57,033
- Okay, bye.
- He lied to me.

333
00:25:57,167 --> 00:25:59,867
He told me
he was just at the office.

334
00:26:00,000 --> 00:26:03,333
No one else was supposed
to know about my illness.

335
00:26:03,467 --> 00:26:05,500
Nobody was supposed to see that.

336
00:26:07,267 --> 00:26:09,200
I have alopecia.

337
00:26:09,367 --> 00:26:12,933
My husband has lost all love
for me.

338
00:26:14,167 --> 00:26:16,200
Thea, I can't get caught.

339
00:26:17,233 --> 00:26:18,667
Marj! Marj!

340
00:26:20,067 --> 00:26:21,333
Paolo?
